#!/bin/sh
# Auto-append commit trailers (umbraculum DCO + Cursor co-authorship).
#
# Activation: this hook is the canonical commit-trailer mechanism for
# umbraculum-toolset. Each clone enables it once via:
#
#     git config core.hooksPath scripts/git-hooks
#
# (see CONTRIBUTING.md §"Developer Certificate of Origin (DCO)" at the
# repo root for the full procedure and rationale).
#
# This hook is the reference implementation of the canonical hook sketch
# documented in `cursor-plugins/umbraculum-toolset-common/rules/44-agent-
# commit-cursor-coauthor.mdc` — the umbraculum-toolset dogfoods the same
# DCO + Cursor co-author discipline that the toolset's plugins ship to
# downstream consumers (umbraculum-dev being the primary one). Keeping
# this hook in lockstep with umbraculum-dev's
# `scripts/git-hooks/prepare-commit-msg` is intentional.
#
# Behavior — handles two trailer concerns from the same hook, both via
# `git interpret-trailers --in-place --if-exists addIfDifferent`:
#
#  1. DCO Signed-off-by (mandatory for umbraculum projects):
#     - Reads GIT_COMMITTER_IDENT (= user.name + user.email) for the
#       signer.
#     - Idempotent: `addIfDifferent` is a no-op if the same trailer is
#       already present (so manual `git commit -s` keeps working without
#       producing duplicates).
#     - No-op on merge / squash commits (those carry their own trailer
#       aggregation rules).
#     - See cursor-plugins/umbraculum-toolset-common/rules/42-dco-
#       signoff-gate.mdc for the full DCO contract.
#
#  2. Cursor co-authorship (per umbraculum MANIFESTO §1.2):
#     - When CURSOR_AGENT=1 is exported in the env (Cursor exports this
#       into every agent tool-call shell, verifiable with `env | grep -i
#       cursor`), this hook ensures Co-authored-by: Cursor
#       <cursoragent@cursor.com> is present in the commit's trailer
#       block.
#     - Fires ONLY when CURSOR_AGENT=1 is set, so human contributors
#       typing `git commit` in their own terminal are never
#       over-attributed.
#     - Idempotent (same `addIfDifferent` semantics).
#     - No-op on merge / squash commits.
#     - See cursor-plugins/umbraculum-toolset-common/rules/44-agent-
#       commit-cursor-coauthor.mdc for the agent-side post-commit
#       verification rule.
#
# Why `git interpret-trailers` instead of raw `printf` appends:
# A previous revision of this hook appended trailers directly via
# `printf '\n%s\n' "$TRAILER" >> "$COMMIT_MSG_FILE"`. That approach
# broke when the commit-message file already ended with a trailer (e.g.
# Cursor's git integration does sometimes pre-inject `Co-authored-by:
# Cursor` into COMMIT_EDITMSG before this hook runs — non-
# deterministically; observed empirically). The unconditional leading
# blank line in the raw append separated the existing trailer from the
# newly-appended one, splitting the file into two trailer paragraphs,
# of which git's trailer parser (`%(trailers)`, GitHub's commit-page
# "Co-authors" UI, PR-author summary panes) only recognizes the LAST
# as trailers — silently classifying the pre-existing trailer as
# message body. `git interpret-trailers` knows the trailer-block rules
# and correctly merges new trailers into the existing block, regardless
# of whether the file already has trailers from another source.
#
# Cursor's pre-injection behavior is opaque and non-deterministic, so
# this hook does NOT depend on it firing — it adds the Co-authored-by
# trailer when CURSOR_AGENT=1 regardless, and `addIfDifferent` makes
# the operation idempotent whether or not Cursor pre-injected. The hook
# is the project's operational contract; any Cursor-side pre-injection
# (when it fires) is additive but not load-bearing.

COMMIT_MSG_FILE=$1
COMMIT_SOURCE=$2

case "$COMMIT_SOURCE" in
  merge|squash) exit 0 ;;
esac

# 1. DCO Signed-off-by injection.
SOB=$(git var GIT_COMMITTER_IDENT | sed -n 's/^\(.*>\).*$/Signed-off-by: \1/p')
if [ -n "$SOB" ]; then
  git interpret-trailers --in-place \
    --if-exists addIfDifferent \
    --trailer "$SOB" \
    "$COMMIT_MSG_FILE"
fi

# 2. Cursor co-author injection (only when running inside a Cursor agent shell).
if [ "${CURSOR_AGENT:-}" = "1" ]; then
  git interpret-trailers --in-place \
    --if-exists addIfDifferent \
    --trailer "Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>" \
    "$COMMIT_MSG_FILE"
fi
